comments.body:
I've also just testing this using `#fork`, but the memory consumed is simply too great:
```ruby
      puts "Transforming the Documents for Solr..."
      xml_documents.each_slice(5) do |xml_doc_subset|
        fork do
          print '.'
          indexer.process_with(xml_doc_subset, solr_documents)
        end
      end
      Process.waitall
```
This seems to be reasonably faster when using Sidekiq and asynchronous job processing.
